2 INTRODUCED BY T. FALK
3
4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING THE CENTRAL COMMITTEE COUNTY CONVENTION
5 NOTIFICATION PROCESS; PROVIDING THAT NOTIFICATION OF THE CALL OF THE COUNTY
6 CONVENTION BE SENT THROUGH ELECTRONIC MAIL TO COMMITTEE REPRESENTATIVES INSTEAD
7 OF CONVENTIONAL MAIL; AND AMENDING SECTION 13-38-205, MCA.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 Section 1. Section 13-38-205, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "13-38-205. Organization and operation of county and city central committees. (1) The county
13 central committee shall meet prior to the state convention of its political party and organize by electing a
14 presiding officer and one or more vice presiding officers. The gender of the presiding officer and the vice
15 presiding officer may not be the same. The county central committee shall elect a secretary and other officers
16 as necessary. It is not necessary for the officers to be precinct committee representatives.
17 (2) The committee may select managing or executive committees and authorize subcommittees to
18 exercise all powers conferred upon the county, city, state, and congressional central committees by the election
19 laws of this state.
20 (3) The presiding officer of the county central committee shall call the county convention and not
21 less than 4 days before the date of the county convention shall publish the call in a newspaper published at the
22 county seat and mail send through electronic mail a copy of the call to each precinct committee representative.
23 If party rules permit the use of a proxy, a proxy may not be recognized unless it is held by an elector of the
24 precinct of the committee representative executing it.
25 (4) The county presiding officer of the party shall preside at the county convention. No person
26 other than a duly elected or appointed committee representative or officer of the committee is entitled to
27 participate in the proceedings of the committee.
28 (5) If a committee representative is absent, the convention may fill the vacancy by appointing some
